The paper discusses an algorithm for parallelizing Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of statistics and exploration-exploitation tradeoff, which are common topics in machine learning and reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions a proprietary benchmark, which suggests that it may be related to industry applications, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category. The paper also discusses game benchmarks, which suggests that it may be related to game theory, making cs.GT (Game Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper may also be related to distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category.
